Hello Jeff, on May 31 you wrote:

> Are there any means of determining how 'bright' a light to use based on
> wattages?  What I mean is, is there any way to equate the values in Imagine
> with the wattage rating on a RL light-bulb, and if so, how?  ...  Also, in
> the FAQ, it says that we can use values greater than 255 for lights...?
> Does this actually work, or does Imagine simply treat values greater than
> 255 as being equal to 255?

The manual states that for reference purposes you can consider a
255,255,255 light a 255 watt light bulb and a 128,128,128 a 128 watt light
bulb and so on.

