@node IML-53 " MSG-53  Subject: Re: Lighting Calculations
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Lighting Calculations
Date:    Saturday, 03 June 1995 07:48:59 
From:    cjo@esrange.ssc.se


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> Are there any means of determining how 'bright' a light to use based on
> wattages? What I mean is, is there any way to equate the values in Imagin=
e
> with the wattage rating on a RL light-bulb, and if so, how?

No. There is no such "conversion method".
Since the effect of a lightbulb decreases with the square of the distance
from the bulb in the real world, but in Imagine a lightsource has the same
effect independant of how far from it the light travels.
(I know, I know, there is controlled fall off and such, but that doesn't
decrease with the square either!)

