On Mon, 5 Jun 1995, Charles Blaquiere wrote:
> Did anyone develop a PD texture which has the same effect? (Reminder:
> Solid applies a single color to an entire object, useful when added to
> the parent of an entire group with "Apply to children" activated. It also
> has a fade parameter, to control the intensity of the color; 0.5 means
> the color is applied at 50% strength, leaving the other 50% whatever was
> already on the object)

Ya, I did.  :-) The texture is called SetChild and is included with the
IITextures archive.  The latest is on my home page, but a slightly older
version is gfx/3d/IITextures?.lha on Aminet.  It works with color,
reflectivity, transparency and fog length with seperate fade paramaters
for each.  Enjoy. 

