> frames and gives an insufficent ram for objects warning and chokes.
> 

This is because if you render the sphere particle type in Scanline, it is 
treated as a primitive sphere, with faces. With 6624 spheres, you have a 
LOT of faces to render. This will exhaust the RAM on most PCs, not to 
mention on some low-end SGI machines.

See ya,
      Roger

