Hi All,

I've found one way of generating 640*480 FLC's on a PC (from files 
generated on the Amiga). First get Ad Pro or something similar to convert 
the individual frames to PCX format. On the PC there is a utility to 
convert PCX to FLC. I don't know if it is shareware as I got it on the 
PCGuide coverCD, the one with Vista Pro 3.0 on it. It is very fast and 
converted a 200 frame anim in a couple on mins. I don't know much about 
PC ftp sites but it might be worth having a look at micros.hensa.ac.uk. I 
think the program is called PCX2FLC

If you have not got Ad Pro, use a PC file converter such as 
Graphic Workshop to convert the Amigas iff files on the PC.

Hope that helps....

Sheil

