@node IML-244 " MSG-244  Subject: Re: Atmosphere
@toc contents

Subject: Re: Atmosphere
Date:    Saturday, 10 June 1995 23:00:23 
From:    Ian Smith <iansmith@moose.erie.net>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

On Sat, 10 Jun 1995 Lumbient@aol.com wrote:
> Wait I thought that all processes in rendering are addictive ie. they add all
> the values together. So .5 + .5 = 1.0  Totally opaque(?)!!
> 
> I may be wrong(doubtful though :)

I sure have found that 3d rendering is addictive... :-)  

But no, they are not additive.  Multiply them instead.  An object
with 0.5 in its transparency fields only lets 50% of the light 
through.  A second object further reduces the light by 50%.  So 
0.5*0.5 = 25% of the light gets through, not 0.

--
