>2. Can I change the rotate axis in SPIN/SWEEP effects ?. I try to do 
>some simple skelet of something and then I SWEEP it. If I do the 
>skelet in FRONT/RIGHT view, the result was OK <> in the TOP view --> 
>the result was awful.

It seems to me You do proved Yourself that SPIN and SWEEP are different. Try 
using SWEEP instead of SPIN.
Anyway.
SP & SW always rotate the object along the local Z axis of the object, so 
You can obtain different kind of rotations by moving or rotating the 
object's axes only (select "Transform Axes Only" in the Transformation 
Requester or press the Shft button in interactive mode).

