@node IML-352 " MSG-352  Subject: Imagine & OS/2
@toc contents

Subject: Imagine & OS/2
Date:    Saturday, 17 June 1995 01:31:05 
From:    Charles Blaquiere <blaq@io.org>


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

> From: Zdenek Pizl INF 3 FSE <PIZL@KVT.UJEP.CZ>
> 
> Hi all!
> 
>  I'm fond of OS/2 version of Imagine. Exists it or :-(
>  
>  
>             Thanx, Pizi from Decin

Pizi, (or is that Pizl?)

Currently, Imagine/PC is only available under DOS, Impulse has announced 
a Windows version coming out this year. (Although you should not take 
their schedule too seriously, I hope you know that) I assume the Windows 
version, if properly written, could run under OS/2.

I don't know if it's any help, but Win95 users have reported being able 
to run Imagine (for DOS) from within Win95, by clicking on the "advanced 
options" of the Run DOS Program box, and entering the contents of the 
Imagine-compatible autoexec.bat and config.sys in the appropriate 
fields.

Oh, and welcome to the Imagine Mailing List!


