@toc contents

Subject: Re: Extrusion problem
Date:    Tuesday, 27 June 1995 02:50:15 
From:    rbyrne@3dform.edex.edu.au (Robert Byrne)


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Hello Brad, on Jun 26 you wrote:

>         The task is a simple one. I am in the midst of creating a talon in
> the detail editor. I am at the point where I want to extrude the nail or
> claw at the end of the toe. I have already extruded a primitive disk for
> the toe and curved the end of it in all the way around to produce a nail
> from inside the "skin" of the foot. Now I want to extrude the disk at the
> end into a nail. I have added and formed an open path to extrude along and
> place this in the center of the disk facing out from the toe. I plan to
> extrude with 0 scaling for both the X and Z axis, thus producing a nail
> shaped like my path that ends in gradual point. For some reason every time
> I try to perform the extrusion with the path as the definer it extrudes
> back into the toe in the shape I want instead of out. I have tried rotating
> all the objects 180 degrees, I have tried rotating just the path axis 180
> degrees, and I have tried setting the "Y to path" switch. When I do the
> last the extrusion starts off in the right direction but, for some reason
> the first section is elongated out of proportion and the rest of the
> sections ( I have 5 total) turn at right angles to the first and never come
> to a point. What's frustrating is that the extrusion that goes back into
> the toe each time I try is the exact shape I want. I am using version 3.2.
> Any help would be appreciated.
>                                 later, Brad

It looks like your first attempt was close and would seem that the Y axis
for each point on your path is pointing in the wrong direction.

Instead of rotating the path's axis 180 degrees, rotate the path 180
degrees. Path extrusions follow the Y axis of the path's points in the
positive direction.

Ignore the path's main axis, it's there because every object has to have
one. It does'nt affect the direction of the extrude.


RIGHT VIEW      |
                |
                |  +----+----+----+> Y (point axis)
                |
                |        Path

               Disk

Regards,  Bob

                       @{"           Thread          477" link IML-477}
