@node IML-511 " MSG-511  Subject: Motion Blur
@toc contents

Subject: Motion Blur
Date:    Wednesday, 28 June 1995 23:44:41 
From:    Lumbient@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

After doing some tests I found that most of us have been doing the blur
effect backwards!!!  

For instance if I were rendering 4 extra frames per frame(4:1) I would have
to mix the frames like this:

1      2     3     4
|        |      \     /
|        |         X   <---4 & 3  mixed into X
|        \      /
|           N <--- X & 2 mixed into N
\           /
final frame <---N & 1 mixed into final frame!

This might seem to be backwards but in reality its not!  In real photos and
film the blur seems to actually go foward.  Example...paintball:
 frame #              1                      2                  3           
In reality--->     ===O                 ==O              =O

But you think this
happends --->     O=                 O==             O===

Your brain is really just tricking you!

                                                   ---Lum

                       @{"           Thread          426" link IML-426}
                       @{"  -=> RETURN TO CONTENTS!<=-  " link contents}
@endnode


