> frnum = RIGHT(frame,4,'0').

Impulse in their infinate wisdom decided to change the format from
pic.xxxx to picxxxx without telling anyone.  I presume they changed
it to accomodate the brain-damaged MS-DOS filename restrictions.

If they can change something to help PC's, I think they need to add 
a feature to help Amigas to be fair. How about ARexx? :-) :-)

Seriously, Rexx is available for the PC... OS/2 uses it for inter-
process communicarions.  It would be a MAJOR feature.  I built a
spiral staircase, and it was a pain having to manually create it
when I could have used a macro instead.

--
