  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

Alright, you Imagine gurus, give me your best stuff:

(I'm using 3.2 on a pc)

I've created an altitude map ("John" written in bold black letters on 
a white background).  Made a default sphere added the quick 
attributes of gold and applied the altitude map as a wrap x & z.  

The render makes the letters engraved into the gold metal ball like I 
wanted, but they look like they were engraved with a chisel.  All the 
letters are real bumpy, not smooth, where the engraving took place.

I tried the same thing using a plane, using flat x & z mapping, and 
got the same results.  It is a bug in the software or my brain?

Also what is the best way to create this effect:

A box with a bright light inside it.  As you lift up the corner of 
the box, the light beams and bright light are discovered and 
gradually seen.  The more you open the box, the brighter the light 
gets and the wider and longer the light beams get.

I've played with some fog/filtered objects as light beams, but it 
just isn't looking all that real.  Any suggestions?

Thanks,

