@node IML-538 " MSG-538  Subject: Re: What is NURBS ?
@toc contents

Subject: Re: What is NURBS ?
Date:    Thursday, 29 June 1995 21:32:49 
From:    craigh@fa.disney.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

On Jun 29,  1:41pm, imagine-relay@email.sp.paramax.com wrote:
>

> I heard the word NURBS used in one of the previous Email's and I have seen it
> elsewhere, could somebody explain it to me?
>-- End of excerpt from imagine-relay@email.sp.paramax.com

Non-uniform rational b-spline (NURBS).  It's a special type of spline that
allows more intuitive control over surface modelling than a lot of other spline
methods.  Surfaces have control points that are used to deform the surface of
the object which is represented by mathematical formulas rather than polygons.




