@node IML-542 " MSG-542  Subject: Fwd: mapping & light
@toc contents

Subject: Fwd: mapping & light
Date:    Thursday, 29 June 1995 23:52:28 
From:    SGiff68285@aol.com


  ----------------------------------------------------------------------------  

In a message dated 95-06-29 18:51:04 EDT, SGiff68285 writes:

<< In a message dated 95-06-29 16:28:37 EDT, you write:

>I've created an altitude map ("John" written in bold black letters on 
>a white background).  Made a default sphere added the quick 
>attributes of gold and applied the altitude map as a wrap x & z.  

The altitude map you used needs to be a anti-aliased image to start with.
 Then make sure that the there are no imperfections or specs in the image.
 This should create a smooth looking effect.  The best way to create
anti-aliased image maps is by creating an image in Adobe Illustrator or
Coreldraw, and then exporting as AI.EPS.  Bring the AI file into Photoshop
and make sure anti-aliasing is turned on.

As far as the box of light.  You were on the right track.  Use the Linear
function and animate the axis of your linear object to create the effect of
the light moving up and out of the box.  

S.G. >>


